<dl id="n25076i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25076i">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25076i"> 76(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> K hears them crying / in China for / baptism</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The majority of Christendom still attaches enormous importance to infant baptism, an importance which is shared, for less precise reasons, by rustics, who believe that &lsquo;children never thrive till they&apos;re christened,&rsquo; and that night air thrills to <mark>the cry of the homeless souls of the unbaptized</mark>. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 104-5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14045g" href="c14all.htm#c14045g">VI.C.14:045(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
